1
00:00:12,367 --> 00:00:13,767
<i> You're the best my FF!</i>

2
00:00:13,900 --> 00:00:15,933
<i> My wing and forever friend.</i>

3
00:00:16,067 --> 00:00:19,700
<i>It's like you're the one who has
parents working hard in America.</i>

4
00:00:19,833 --> 00:00:21,033
<i> She gave these to me.</i>

5
00:00:21,167 --> 00:00:23,700
<i>That's because
you're fooling her.</i>

6
00:00:23,833 --> 00:00:27,000
<i>Auntie, don't accuse
Betsy like that.</i>

7
00:00:32,433 --> 00:00:33,833
<i> Did you get hurt?</i>

8
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:35,433
<i> No, not at all.</i>

9
00:00:35,567 --> 00:00:36,467
<i> Thank you.</i>

10
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:37,500
<i> That's nothing.</i>

11
00:00:37,633 --> 00:00:38,967
<i>- Gerald?
- Hey.</i>

12
00:00:39,100 --> 00:00:41,100
<i>Have you and Gerald known
each other for a long time?</i>

13
00:00:41,233 --> 00:00:42,400
<i> Is he your type?</i>

14
00:00:42,533 --> 00:00:43,467
<i> You said you were close.</i>

15
00:00:43,600 --> 00:00:44,867
<i>Maybe you're the one
who likes him?</i>

16
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:46,200
<i> He's just my friend!</i>

17
00:00:46,333 --> 00:00:48,100
<i>Are you going to wear the
dress that I gave to your mom?</i>

18
00:00:48,233 --> 00:00:50,300
<i>Because I was inspired
by your stories</i>

19
00:00:50,433 --> 00:00:52,700
<i>that Mommy used that dress
at your prom.</i>

20
00:00:52,833 --> 00:00:53,933
<i> Why did you wear that?</i>

21
00:00:54,067 --> 00:00:56,300
<i>Didn't I say, that's what
I'll wear on my birthday?</i>

22
00:00:56,433 --> 00:00:58,967
<i>If you wear it, will you forget
that your parents left you?</i>

23
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:00,700
<i> That is so mean!</i>

24
00:01:00,833 --> 00:01:04,933
<i>Sorry, because I'm poor so I'm
counting on your donations!</i>

25
00:01:05,067 --> 00:01:06,867
<i> But remember,</i>

26
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:10,200
<i>even if you have a lot of nice
things and other friends...</i>

27
00:01:11,533 --> 00:01:13,600
<i>you won't find
a best friend like me!</i>

28
00:01:13,733 --> 00:01:17,033
<i>Let us all welcome
our lovely birthday celebrant,</i>

29
00:01:17,167 --> 00:01:20,567
<i> Ms. Gina Marie Rodriguez!</i>

30
00:01:20,700 --> 00:01:23,033
<i>Thank you for choosing me
as your escort.</i>

31
00:01:23,167 --> 00:01:25,867
<i>I hope I can make
your whole night happy.</i>

32
00:01:40,333 --> 00:01:42,133
Why do you look sad?

33
00:01:42,300 --> 00:01:43,833
Is there a problem?

34
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:48,233
I miss my parents.

35
00:01:49,267 --> 00:01:51,433
How I wish they were here.

36
00:01:52,967 --> 00:01:56,133
But they can't be
with me on all the occasions.

37
00:01:58,633 --> 00:02:05,200
Who knows on your next birthday,
or Christmas or New Year, right?

38
00:02:05,333 --> 00:02:10,500
So just smile, they might think
you don't want to dance with me.

39
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:12,767
What?

40
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:15,433
I like you.

41
00:02:15,567 --> 00:02:16,700
I mean...

42
00:02:16,833 --> 00:02:18,633
I want to dance with you.

43
00:02:19,667 --> 00:02:21,300
Me too, I like you too.

44
00:02:22,833 --> 00:02:23,633
What?

45
00:02:25,300 --> 00:02:27,667
I want to spin you around.

46
00:03:25,833 --> 00:03:29,167
Hey, you look like in love!

47
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:33,300
Cheers to the newlyweds!

48
00:03:57,200 --> 00:04:00,033
Oh my gosh,
they're such a sweet couple.

49
00:04:00,167 --> 00:04:02,233
- True.
- Girl, who's the guy?

50
00:04:02,367 --> 00:04:05,000
Gina is hiding her
boyfriend from us.

51
00:04:05,133 --> 00:04:07,200
They look so good together.

52
00:04:07,333 --> 00:04:09,367
It's so noisy here, let me pass.

53
00:04:14,100 --> 00:04:15,567
- Happy Birthday Gina!
- Happy Birthday Gina!

54
00:04:15,700 --> 00:04:17,800
Thank you.
Go ahead and eat first.

55
00:04:17,933 --> 00:04:19,233
Go, go, go.

56
00:04:22,433 --> 00:04:25,100
Gina, happy birthday again.

57
00:04:25,233 --> 00:04:25,867
- Thank you.
- Sorry,

58
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,433
I wasn't able to buy
a gift.

59
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:30,933
The pictures I took of you and
Gerald, they're beautiful.

60
00:04:31,067 --> 00:04:34,367
They're so sweet.

61
00:04:34,500 --> 00:04:37,367
Maybe he was just
trying to be nice.

62
00:04:37,500 --> 00:04:39,500
If Gerald will court you,
will you answer him?

63
00:04:39,633 --> 00:04:40,233
What?

64
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:44,467
Excuse me.

65
00:04:46,167 --> 00:04:47,967
- Hello.
- Hi. Good Evening.

66
00:04:48,100 --> 00:04:49,867
- Good evening.
- Gina, excuse me.

67
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:52,267
Gina, we have visitors
who came for you.

68
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:55,133
- Come.
- Excuse me, excuse me.

69
00:05:01,467 --> 00:05:05,000
Ladies and Gentlemen,
give a huge round of applause

70
00:05:05,133 --> 00:05:09,167
for Mr. and Mrs. Rodriguez.

71
00:05:14,567 --> 00:05:15,633
Mommy.

72
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:19,067
Mommy...

73
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:21,267
Daddy.

74
00:05:32,033 --> 00:05:33,733
Why didn't you tell me?

75
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:35,167
Then it wouldn't be
a surprise anymore.

76
00:05:35,300 --> 00:05:38,000
- Happy Birthday.
- Happy Birthday!

77
00:05:38,133 --> 00:05:39,700
And this is for you.

78
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:42,300
Open it.

79
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:47,000
Dad, Mom, thank you.

80
00:05:47,133 --> 00:05:48,267
Did you like it?

81
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:49,500
It's beautiful.

82
00:05:50,833 --> 00:05:51,733
Here, let me put
that on for you.

83
00:05:53,533 --> 00:05:55,867
This looks perfect
on you for sure.

84
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,500
Your Mom and I
searched for this.

85
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:03,700
This is the first necklace
for you.

86
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:11,733
- This is challenging.
- It's so beautiful.

87
00:06:11,867 --> 00:06:14,100
Okay, ready.

88
00:06:14,233 --> 00:06:16,133
Wow.

89
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:19,300
Beautiful.

90
00:06:21,067 --> 00:06:22,500
Very challenging.

91
00:06:22,633 --> 00:06:24,133
Okay, there it is.

92
00:06:24,267 --> 00:06:27,133
- So beautiful!
- Okay, let's fix it.

93
00:06:27,267 --> 00:06:28,467
There you go.

94
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:30,233
- Beautiful.
- Perfect.

95
00:06:31,500 --> 00:06:34,467
Even if I wanted you to be here.

96
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:38,200
I didn't expect that
you'll be coming home.

97
00:06:38,333 --> 00:06:42,267
This is what I always wish
for every birthday of mine.

98
00:06:42,433 --> 00:06:44,333
I wish to be with you...

99
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:48,900
that's why thank you,
Mom and Dad.

100
00:06:49,767 --> 00:06:51,033
Thank you.

101
00:06:51,167 --> 00:06:52,267
My child,

102
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:56,900
I'm sorry because we know
there are important days

103
00:06:57,033 --> 00:06:59,100
that your Mom and I
failed to go to.

104
00:07:00,100 --> 00:07:04,567
And we're sorry
if sometimes you feel alone

105
00:07:04,700 --> 00:07:07,600
and we can't come back
for you here.

106
00:07:07,733 --> 00:07:10,200
I'm sorry also
for the many excuses

107
00:07:10,333 --> 00:07:14,967
that we can't come to see you.

108
00:07:15,133 --> 00:07:16,500
We're always here for you.

109
00:07:17,667 --> 00:07:21,667
And Gina, you understand me
and your Daddy, right?

110
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:26,233
We just want you to be happy
and successful in this life.

111
00:07:26,367 --> 00:07:28,600
I appreciate that.

112
00:07:28,733 --> 00:07:31,700
I'm so thankful to you...

113
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:35,233
but being loved by you...

114
00:07:35,367 --> 00:07:38,667
is more than enough
to make me happy.

115
00:07:48,967 --> 00:07:50,267
There's your Auntie.

116
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:52,500
Auntie, I'm so happy!

117
00:07:52,633 --> 00:07:54,767
Thank you.

118
00:07:58,967 --> 00:08:00,300
Come here, come here.

119
00:08:01,733 --> 00:08:03,433
Hug.

120
00:08:03,567 --> 00:08:05,033
Group hug.

121
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:08,467
Are you okay now?

122
00:08:09,967 --> 00:08:11,100
That's tears of joy.

123
00:08:12,867 --> 00:08:14,567
- Okay.
- Auntie.

124
00:08:24,133 --> 00:08:27,667
Hey Gina,
where did you meet your escort?

125
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:28,967
That's Gerald.

126
00:08:29,100 --> 00:08:30,833
He's a friend of Betsy.

127
00:08:30,967 --> 00:08:32,800
Oh, Betsy.

128
00:08:32,933 --> 00:08:34,667
Isn't she your best friend?

129
00:08:34,800 --> 00:08:37,467
Yes, so be nice to her, okay?

130
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:39,667
Hey, we're nice.

131
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:42,233
She's the one with an attitude
towards us earlier.

132
00:08:42,367 --> 00:08:43,400
Don't mind her.

133
00:08:43,533 --> 00:08:44,833
Tell us more about Gerald.

134
00:08:46,867 --> 00:08:48,033
Excuse me.

135
00:08:48,167 --> 00:08:49,200
Let me in for a while.

136
00:08:49,333 --> 00:08:50,667
How are you?

137
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:51,933
Who is that Gerald?

138
00:08:52,067 --> 00:08:53,167
- I've been hearing his name.
- That's right.

139
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:55,267
It's Gina's future boyfriend.

140
00:08:55,433 --> 00:08:56,933
Oh, future boyfriend?

141
00:08:57,067 --> 00:08:59,167
Gina, you're still young
for that.

142
00:08:59,300 --> 00:09:00,667
That hurts my feelings.

143
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:04,067
Don't mind them, Dad.

144
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,733
As long I'm enjoying it.

145
00:09:05,867 --> 00:09:08,067
All the special people
in my life are here.

146
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:09,900
- Of course.
- That's you, Mom,

147
00:09:10,033 --> 00:09:12,700
Auntie Connie and Betsy.

148
00:09:12,833 --> 00:09:14,233
That's good.

149
00:09:14,367 --> 00:09:15,800
Oh, maybe this is the person

150
00:09:15,933 --> 00:09:17,400
your Auntie Connie
is telling me about.

151
00:09:17,533 --> 00:09:20,533
Betsy, she's such
a troublemaker, right?

152
00:09:20,667 --> 00:09:21,967
Is she the one?

153
00:09:27,033 --> 00:09:28,933
Maybe not. Maybe that kid
is just adventurous.

154
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:32,667
- Okay.
- But this Gerald...

155
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:33,733
Is he here?

156
00:09:33,867 --> 00:09:35,567
So I can check him out.

157
00:09:37,467 --> 00:09:39,200
He's okay, Dad.

158
00:09:39,333 --> 00:09:40,400
He's okay.

159
00:09:40,533 --> 00:09:42,933
That's why I chose him
to be my escort.

160
00:09:44,767 --> 00:09:45,967
- Okay.
- Okay.

161
00:09:46,100 --> 00:09:47,200
- Yes.
- Is he there?

162
00:09:47,333 --> 00:09:48,400
So I can meet him.

163
00:09:49,933 --> 00:09:51,467
FF!

164
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:53,400
FF!

165
00:09:53,533 --> 00:09:56,400
I'm so happy!

166
00:09:56,533 --> 00:09:58,767
Daddy and Mommy made
a huge effort to surprise me,

167
00:09:58,900 --> 00:09:59,700
didn't they?

168
00:09:59,833 --> 00:10:01,400
Is that really the only reason?

169
00:10:01,567 --> 00:10:04,900
You looked so happy earlier when
you and Gerald were dancing.

170
00:10:05,033 --> 00:10:07,033
Is that so? Is it obvious?

171
00:10:07,167 --> 00:10:08,567
Of course!

172
00:10:08,700 --> 00:10:10,800
Gerald's a gentleman.

173
00:10:10,933 --> 00:10:12,967
He's so nice.

174
00:10:13,100 --> 00:10:15,467
That's probably
why you noticed me

175
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:18,133
because I enjoy
when I'm with Gerald.

176
00:10:21,433 --> 00:10:23,033
I think I like him.

177
00:10:23,167 --> 00:10:26,767
If I ever have a boyfriend,
I want someone like Gerald.

178
00:10:28,433 --> 00:10:31,033
This night is perfect.

179
00:10:31,167 --> 00:10:33,700
Best birthday ever!

180
00:10:45,433 --> 00:10:47,467
Mackie, where's Gerald?

181
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:49,600
Why are you suddenly looking
for him?

182
00:10:49,733 --> 00:10:51,567
Are you going to chase him now?

183
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:54,733
You know my best friend
likes someone else.

184
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:17,767
Well, let's see.

185
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:27,867
Gerald!

186
00:11:32,767 --> 00:11:34,533
Are you still mad at me?

187
00:11:35,533 --> 00:11:38,767
- I'm sorry!
- You don't need to be sorry.

188
00:11:38,900 --> 00:11:42,700
What can I do if you just think
of me as a friend, right?

189
00:11:42,867 --> 00:11:44,667
Is that how you perceived it?

190
00:11:46,067 --> 00:11:49,033
What if I told you
that I like you too?

191
00:11:51,467 --> 00:11:54,633
Does this mean we're a couple?

192
00:12:22,333 --> 00:12:24,500
Maybe you want someone else.

193
00:12:24,633 --> 00:12:25,933
None.

194
00:12:26,067 --> 00:12:27,967
Just you, Betsy.

195
00:12:28,100 --> 00:12:30,767
I love you, since then.

196
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:33,467
And like you always say,

197
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:36,500
you can count on me
for everything...

198
00:12:36,633 --> 00:12:38,500
because I love you so much.

199
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:51,333
Happy birthday to you.
Happy birthday to you.

200
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:59,800
Happy birthday, Happy birthday,
Happy birthday to you!

201
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,233
Oh, make a wish!

202
00:13:12,767 --> 00:13:15,433
Gina, I think I know
what you wished for...

203
00:13:15,567 --> 00:13:17,367
to be with me and your daddy.

204
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:19,600
You know what, this year,

205
00:13:19,733 --> 00:13:23,133
your dream of being with us
in America will come true!

206
00:13:24,233 --> 00:13:25,567
That's what you want, right?

207
00:13:27,500 --> 00:13:28,500
All right.

208
00:13:28,633 --> 00:13:30,500
We're just waiting
for the petition to come out.

209
00:13:30,633 --> 00:13:32,767
After that,
you'll just finish your semester

210
00:13:32,900 --> 00:13:33,833
and then we'll go straight.

211
00:13:33,967 --> 00:13:36,300
- We will all live in America.
- Yes!

212
00:13:36,433 --> 00:13:37,433
- It's true!
- Really?

213
00:13:37,567 --> 00:13:40,833
Yes, and I promise you
we'll make it up to you.

214
00:13:41,933 --> 00:13:43,700
- Really?
- Yes.

215
00:13:43,833 --> 00:13:46,567
I've been waiting
for this for a long time.

216
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:49,733
- It's a dream come true!
- Yes, yes, yes, yes.

217
00:14:00,067 --> 00:14:01,733
Happy birthday!

218
00:14:01,867 --> 00:14:03,400
Happy birthday,
happy birthday.

219
00:14:03,533 --> 00:14:05,233
- Thank you, thank you!
- Happy birthday.

220
00:14:06,633 --> 00:14:08,100
Thank you, Mom.

221
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:10,400
Hang out with your friends.

222
00:14:10,533 --> 00:14:12,167
- Your Dad and I can manage.
- Thank you!

223
00:14:12,300 --> 00:14:13,500
Hang out with them.

224
00:14:32,767 --> 00:14:35,300
Gina, are you okay?

225
00:14:35,433 --> 00:14:36,567
- Are you all right?
- Yes.

226
00:14:38,233 --> 00:14:43,367
I didn't expect this
but it's all of a sudden.

227
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:44,867
I'm going to live in the US.

228
00:14:45,933 --> 00:14:48,000
Good. That's what you really
want, isn't it?

229
00:14:48,133 --> 00:14:49,233
Yes.

230
00:14:49,367 --> 00:14:51,300
I was just surprised.

231
00:14:51,433 --> 00:14:52,567
Yeah.

232
00:14:52,700 --> 00:14:56,867
Okay. I know, you're used
to being with your friends

233
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:58,367
here in the Philippines.

234
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:02,200
But I also want you
to open your doors.

235
00:15:02,367 --> 00:15:04,167
Meet new friends,

236
00:15:04,300 --> 00:15:05,333
do new things, okay?

237
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:08,600
I want you to be happy.
That's all I want.

238
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:11,467
But, Dad...

239
00:15:12,700 --> 00:15:15,533
What if I make a mistake
in trusting someone?

240
00:15:17,767 --> 00:15:20,233
Like you were betrayed?
Something ike that?

241
00:15:20,367 --> 00:15:21,233
Yes.

242
00:15:21,367 --> 00:15:22,900
Yeah.

243
00:15:23,033 --> 00:15:26,767
You know, there are other people
that don't deserve your time

244
00:15:26,900 --> 00:15:28,567
and attention.

245
00:15:28,700 --> 00:15:33,033
Not all those who you consider
friends are your true friends.

246
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:36,833
I don't want you to get hurt,

247
00:15:36,967 --> 00:15:39,933
and I don't want you
to be fooled by anyone.

248
00:15:41,700 --> 00:15:44,000
You deserve more than that...

249
00:15:44,133 --> 00:15:46,233
much, much more than that.

250
00:16:21,800 --> 00:16:22,333
Gina...

251
00:16:23,367 --> 00:16:25,367
I want to tell you something.

252
00:16:28,900 --> 00:16:29,767
What?

253
00:16:31,233 --> 00:16:32,633
Are you and Gerald together?

254
00:16:34,133 --> 00:16:36,633
I already knew that
because I saw you earlier.

255
00:16:38,433 --> 00:16:40,167
Sorry, Gina.

256
00:16:40,300 --> 00:16:42,133
We didn't mean it.

257
00:16:43,733 --> 00:16:45,067
We suddenly became a couple.

258
00:16:46,100 --> 00:16:47,267
It just happened.

259
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:50,867
What about what
I shared with you?

260
00:16:52,800 --> 00:16:54,000
I confessed...

261
00:16:55,167 --> 00:16:57,500
that I liked Gerald, didn't I?

262
00:16:57,633 --> 00:16:59,533
I asked you.

263
00:16:59,667 --> 00:17:02,633
You said you don't like him.

264
00:17:04,133 --> 00:17:06,933
Wait, I didn't say
anything like that.

265
00:17:08,233 --> 00:17:10,900
Maybe you just misunderstood.

266
00:17:11,033 --> 00:17:13,900
Besides, why would you react
like you were robbed?

267
00:17:15,467 --> 00:17:18,267
You know that Gerald
really wants me, right?

268
00:17:20,267 --> 00:17:21,600
I didn't know that.

269
00:17:22,667 --> 00:17:27,267
If you just said that you
both like each other,

270
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:30,333
I would be happy for you because
you're my best friend.

271
00:17:30,467 --> 00:17:33,900
Well, I'm already explaining
that we didn't mean it.

272
00:17:34,033 --> 00:17:36,033
Why don't you believe me?

273
00:17:40,867 --> 00:17:42,767
Betsy...

274
00:17:42,900 --> 00:17:44,600
please.

275
00:17:44,733 --> 00:17:46,200
It's my birthday.

276
00:17:46,333 --> 00:17:48,133
I don't want to ruin my night.

277
00:17:48,300 --> 00:17:49,800
So what do you want to say,

278
00:17:49,933 --> 00:17:52,467
that I'm the one ruining
your birthday.

279
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:54,000
Don't be paranoid.

280
00:17:54,133 --> 00:17:55,600
Don't play the victim either.

281
00:17:56,867 --> 00:17:58,833
Why are you annoyed?

282
00:17:58,967 --> 00:17:59,867
That I got ahead of you?

283
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:01,967
You lied to me!

284
00:18:02,100 --> 00:18:05,467
Because if you do care about me,
you should have been honest!

285
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:07,067
But you made me
look like a fool!

286
00:18:07,200 --> 00:18:09,033
Wow! Is that the one
who looks like a fool?

287
00:18:09,167 --> 00:18:10,367
Your birthday
is already so grand,

288
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:13,400
everyone finds you beautiful
and your parents even came!

289
00:18:13,533 --> 00:18:15,867
So you have no right
to complain!

290
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:16,700
You know what?

291
00:18:16,833 --> 00:18:17,967
You're right!

292
00:18:18,100 --> 00:18:20,800
I should still be happy because
Daddy and Mom will take me.

293
00:18:20,933 --> 00:18:22,667
I'm going to live
in the States soon!

294
00:18:22,833 --> 00:18:25,000
You know, Gina,
you are arrogant!

295
00:18:25,133 --> 00:18:26,867
You know how arrogant you are!

296
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:28,267
You are so arrogant!

297
00:18:37,767 --> 00:18:39,600
Betsy, Gina!

298
00:18:47,700 --> 00:18:50,333
Gina!

299
00:18:50,467 --> 00:18:51,900
- Come here!
- Gina, Gina!

300
00:18:52,033 --> 00:18:54,533
- I'm tired of you!
- Stop it, stop it!

301
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:57,233
- Stop it! Break them up!
- Gina, Gina, Gina.

302
00:18:57,367 --> 00:18:58,467
- Let go, let go!
- That's enough!

303
00:18:58,600 --> 00:18:59,533
Stop it, Betsy!

304
00:19:01,100 --> 00:19:02,800
Stop it, Betsy!

305
00:19:02,933 --> 00:19:04,800
Let go of me, Gerald!

306
00:19:04,933 --> 00:19:06,200
You're so arrogant, Gina!

307
00:19:06,333 --> 00:19:07,600
Stop it, Betsy!

308
00:19:14,600 --> 00:19:15,367
Hey!

309
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:17,333
What's going on here?

310
00:19:17,467 --> 00:19:18,133
Gina!

311
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:20,800
Aunt Connie,

312
00:19:20,933 --> 00:19:22,567
it's no big deal.

313
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:24,733
It's both our fault,
we miscalculated the steps

314
00:19:24,867 --> 00:19:26,800
that's why we fell.

315
00:19:26,933 --> 00:19:29,867
Gina, go up now and get dressed!

316
00:19:30,033 --> 00:19:31,033
Do it now!

317
00:19:33,100 --> 00:19:34,000
And all of you...

318
00:19:34,133 --> 00:19:38,133
Especially you, go home,
the party is over!

319
00:19:43,933 --> 00:19:45,333
You're annoying!

320
00:19:47,700 --> 00:19:48,800
And you too!

321
00:19:48,933 --> 00:19:50,100
You're all annoying!

322
00:19:50,233 --> 00:19:51,633
This is all your fault!

323
00:19:53,167 --> 00:19:54,400
What?

324
00:19:54,533 --> 00:19:56,033
Are you just going
to stand there?

325
00:19:57,133 --> 00:19:58,633
Go ahead!

326
00:19:58,767 --> 00:19:59,900
You're all like that!

327
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:03,300
Whatever.

328
00:20:10,667 --> 00:20:11,767
Betsy.

329
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:19,300
Here.

330
00:20:19,433 --> 00:20:21,933
There are some clothes
there so you can change.

331
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:26,833
Gina...

332
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:31,300
you shouldn't be angry
with me anymore.

333
00:20:31,433 --> 00:20:34,000
You can get everything you want.

334
00:20:34,133 --> 00:20:37,100
But I'm also sharing
it all with you.

335
00:20:37,267 --> 00:20:39,033
Even so.

336
00:20:39,167 --> 00:20:41,033
You're still leaving in the end.

337
00:20:42,233 --> 00:20:44,833
Meanwhile, I feel like
a pitiful person here.

338
00:20:45,833 --> 00:20:49,433
And you, you are just going
to have fun in America?

339
00:20:49,567 --> 00:20:51,200
That's what you think.

340
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:53,100
I feel sad,

341
00:20:53,233 --> 00:20:56,233
because I thought
I had a true friend,

342
00:20:56,367 --> 00:20:58,333
someone I could keep forever.

343
00:20:58,467 --> 00:21:02,000
Even though I'm in the US
or wherever I am.

344
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:04,833
But I guess I'm wrong.

345
00:21:06,067 --> 00:21:08,233
<i>If you don't want me to be
your friend anymore,</i>

346
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:10,033
<i>then I won't show myself to you!</i>

347
00:21:10,167 --> 00:21:13,333
<i>Sorry if you misinterpreted me.
I was just really surprised.</i>

348
00:21:13,467 --> 00:21:15,600
<i>It's easy to repair
a ruined dress.</i>

349
00:21:15,733 --> 00:21:19,500
<i>But if our friendship is broken,
it's hard to get it back.</i>

350
00:21:21,133 --> 00:21:24,367
I'm missing half of my wings.

351
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:26,867
But I know that
I will still be okay.

352
00:21:28,800 --> 00:21:31,900
Because this
isn't the life for me.

353
00:21:32,033 --> 00:21:34,233
I belong in the US,

354
00:21:34,367 --> 00:21:35,767
with my parents.

355
00:21:38,133 --> 00:21:39,600
So, I guess it's all good.

356
00:21:54,867 --> 00:21:57,267
Thank you for everything.

357
00:21:57,400 --> 00:21:59,200
Be happy.

358
00:22:00,567 --> 00:22:05,133
I really wish that you would be
content with what you have now.

359
00:22:18,967 --> 00:22:20,800
Goodbye, Betsy.

360
00:22:43,667 --> 00:22:44,667
Debbie, can you make sure

361
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:47,667
that our next shipment
comes on Thursday, please?

362
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:48,867
Wait. What?

363
00:22:49,033 --> 00:22:51,700
You endorsed all of that
to me last week because you said

364
00:22:51,833 --> 00:22:54,467
you and Mark were going on
an out-of-town trip, right?

365
00:22:54,600 --> 00:22:56,333
Wait a minute!

366
00:22:56,467 --> 00:22:58,567
What's up with you?

367
00:22:58,700 --> 00:23:01,400
Debbie, it's the shipment
we're talking about.

368
00:23:01,533 --> 00:23:04,500
We just cannot compromise
the quality of our products.

369
00:23:07,667 --> 00:23:08,567
Excuse me.

370
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:15,767
From where I stand,

371
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:18,233
it looks like you're
the one being compromised.

372
00:23:18,367 --> 00:23:19,500
I thought you were on leave

373
00:23:19,633 --> 00:23:23,233
for your anniversary
celebration with Mark?

374
00:23:25,900 --> 00:23:27,800
He had a work thing, Dad.

375
00:23:27,933 --> 00:23:29,100
He had to fly to Hong Kong.

376
00:23:29,233 --> 00:23:32,767
But, you know
how demanding his job is, right?

377
00:23:32,900 --> 00:23:34,300
Hey, Gina.

378
00:23:34,433 --> 00:23:35,833
With his talent in business,

379
00:23:35,967 --> 00:23:39,467
he would have just focused
on our business,

380
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:42,933
maybe you could have saved up
for your future.

381
00:23:43,067 --> 00:23:45,800
But it's like he has no interest
in this supermarket.

382
00:23:45,933 --> 00:23:47,633
Hey, Gina.

383
00:23:47,767 --> 00:23:51,167
Do you think that Mark
is serious about you?

384
00:24:00,100 --> 00:24:02,400
Love, I'm here at your place.

385
00:24:02,533 --> 00:24:04,733
I just thought
I'd clean up a bit

386
00:24:04,867 --> 00:24:06,567
before you come back
from Hong Kong.

387
00:24:07,933 --> 00:24:10,333
Nothing. I just really miss you.

388
00:24:10,467 --> 00:24:11,267
Okay?

389
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:12,400
Bye.

390
00:25:17,167 --> 00:25:19,167
Why? What happened?

391
00:25:19,300 --> 00:25:21,200
I caught him with another woman.

392
00:25:21,333 --> 00:25:24,000
You just made a mistake
in loving the wrong person.

393
00:25:24,133 --> 00:25:26,233
Why don't you just go home
to the Philippines?

394
00:25:26,367 --> 00:25:28,467
You need a break
from this breakup.

395
00:25:28,600 --> 00:25:30,133
One of these days, wait.

396
00:25:30,267 --> 00:25:33,600
You'll find a man
who will love you too.

397
00:25:33,733 --> 00:25:34,600
Are you okay?

398
00:25:34,733 --> 00:25:35,900
Gina?

399
00:25:36,067 --> 00:25:37,067
Gerald?

400
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:39,033
Gerald will be the one
to lift me out of poverty,

401
00:25:39,167 --> 00:25:41,067
and I'm getting
something from him!

402
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:42,100
You talk so much!

403
00:25:42,233 --> 00:25:44,000
You haven't proven anything yet!

404
00:25:44,133 --> 00:25:45,700
I'm willing to help in any way.

405
00:25:45,833 --> 00:25:50,100
If you want to speed up the
process of us going to America,

406
00:25:50,233 --> 00:25:52,500
marry Gerald.

407
00:25:52,633 --> 00:25:53,333
What?
